/**
 * @page reference_design Reference Hardware Design
 * @brief A reference hardware design.
 *
 * [TOC]
 *
 * @section ref_overview Overview
 *
 * The reference design is based on the <a
 * href="http://www.microchipdirect.com/ProductSearch.aspx?Keywords=DM320004-2">
 * PIC 32 Ethernet Starter Kit (DM320004-2)</a> which uses a MX795F512L MCU.
 * The <a
 * href="http://www.microchipdirect.com/ProductSearch.aspx?Keywords=DM320003-3">
 * PIC32 USB Starter Kit III (DM320003-3)</a> is cheaper and should also work.
 * The latter uses a MX470F512L MCU so you may need to change some settings.
 *
 * You'll also need an I/O breakout board: <a
 * href="http://www.microchipdirect.com/ProductSearch.aspx?keywords=DM320002">
 * PIC32 I/O Expansion Board (DM320002)</a>
 *
 * @section ref_pin_assignments Pin Assignments
 *
 * On the DM320004-2 starter kit, with the DM320002 I/O board, the pin
 * assignments are as follows:
 *
 * |  Use          | Pin Name    | J1 Connector | J11 Connector | Port  | Bit
 * | ------------- | ----------- | ------------ | ------------- | ----- | ---
 * | UART RX       | SCM1A/RF2   | 88           | 41            | -     | -
 * | UART TX       | SCM1B/RF8   | 90           | 43            | F     | 8
 * | TX Enable     | PMPD11/RF0  | 18           | 7             | F     | 0
 * | RX Enable     | PMPD10/RF1  | 16           | 8             | F     | 1
 * | Input Capture | IC2         | 54           | 26            | -     | -
 * | RDM Identify  | OC4/RD3     | 40           | 18            | D     | 3
 * | RDM Mute      | SS1/IC2/RD9 | 52           | 23            | D     | 10
 *
 * If you use a different MCU, you can change the pin assignments in
 * system_settings.h
 *
 * @section ref_transceiver Transceiver Hardware
 *
 * To build a basic DMX / RDM Transceiver module, you'll need:
 *
 *  - 1 x
 *    <a href="http://datasheets.maximintegrated.com/en/ds/MAX1487-MAX491.pdf">
 *    MAX481CPA</a>
 *  - 2 x 562 &Omega; resistor
 *  - 1 x 133 &Omega; resistor
 *  - 1 x 0.1 &mu;F capacitor
 *  - 1 x 5 pin XLR connector
 *  - 1 x Breakout board connector, or another means of attaching to J11 on the
 *  - 2 LEDs (Mute & Identify status)
 *  I/O expansion board.
 *
 * @note This transceiver is not isolated.
 *
 * @image html transceiver.png "The DMX / RDM Transceiver module"

 *
